title: What is the best ANN search solution with metadata pre-filtering?
text:
Hi HN,
Now that Elasticsearch supports ANN search with pre-filtering, version 8.2 onward, and there are many open source solutions such as Vespa, Weaviate, etc. that could also be easily hosted, what is a good solution to choose for a production system? Is there any benchmarking/comparisons that could be referred to in order to make the choice?

title: A GPT-3 Powered Text-to-SQL Sandbox
Launch HN: Tersho (YC S22) – AI to write and understand spreadsheet formulas
text:
Hey HN, I'm Apoorve, one of the co-founders of Tersho and currently in the YC batch, excited to share our tool to make writing formulas in Google Sheets and Excel easier.

During our previous startup, we faced the problem of using Google Sheets inefficiently, often writing app script code for what could be done with a couple of formulas owing to our lack of knowledge about spreadsheet functions.

So we built Tersho, an AI tool than can write formulas from simple English descriptions. It can also explain complicated formulas simply.

Behind the scenes, we are using OpenAI's Codex and a lot of prompt engineering involving knowledge about all the formulas and lots of labelled examples.

There's a live demo on our website (https://www.tersho.com) and we also have Excel and Google Sheets add-ins available for download.

Happy to hear feedback!

Ask HN: What can I do with my skill set?
text:
I am a civil servant in a developing country overseeing complex administrative and operational tasks wherein I lead teams and negotiate with different stakeholders.

Previously I worked as an engineer and I have over the years leveraged my background in engineering to achieve significant results by automating government workflows.

To an extent, I have kept programming with Python and have used PowerBi for reporting. In addition, I have used GIS for different projects.

What kind of roles are suitable for me if I want to move back to engineering?
